description:
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited from enthusiastic and highly motivated therapy radiographers and qualified students who would like to develop their knowledge, care and skills in a forward thinking and technically advancing department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In line with Trust values, we take pride in providing our patients with the best outcomes of care and an excellent experience whilst in our hospital. By ensuring a skilled and motivated staff group, we aim to best meet patients’ needs and ensure excellent productivity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Arden Cancer Centre provides a full Oncology service of radiotherapy, chemotherapy and outpatients department and a strategic partnership with the Worcestershire Oncology Service. The radiotherapy service has 5 matched Elekta Agility Linacs providing IMRT/IGRT capability, supported with Mosaiq Oncology management system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a rotational post, covering CT scanners, pre treatment workflows as well as treatment delivery. As a good all rounder, you will be working as part of a friendly and well organised group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
